# Project: Bodyjunkies Website Redesign

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 15+ (App Router)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- UI Library: shadcn/ui
- Components: Use 'Lucide-React' for icons.
- Integrations: Momence (Booking & PT scheduling).

## Coding Standards
- Be concise. Do not explain standard code patterns unless asked.
- Use 'Functional Components' only. No Class components.
- Default to 'Server Components' unless interactivity (`useState`, `useEffect`) is strictly required.
- Always aim for 'Mobile-First' design.

## Brand Voice & Copy Constraints (Critical)
- **Anti-Overselling:** Strictly avoid "salesy" language. No mentions of "discounts," "save money," "limited time offers," or "act now".
- **Tone:** Let the vibe and expert coaching speak for itself. Focus on grit, power, and the "inner fire".

## UI/UX & Navigation Rules
- **The "Strong Gateway" Pattern:** Hero sections should prioritize high-impact video over text.
- **User Segmentation:** Use a "Beginner vs. Experienced" fork early in the funnel:
  - Beginner: Focus on the "one with gloves" (Starter Pack).
  - Experienced: Focus on equipment and booking sessions.
- **Concise Layouts:** Avoid "endless scrolls." Keep pages tight and move detailed "About Us" or technical info to dedicated sub-pages.
- **PT Integration:** Every Personal Training section must leverage the Momence integration and include a lead form for goals/situation assessment.

## The "Wow Factor" Guidelines
- **Visuals:** Use the [BLOK London](https://www.bloklondon.com/) aesthetic as a benchmark: high contrast, minimalist, heavy typography.
- **Interactions:** Implement subtle micro-interactions on all interactive elements using `framer-motion`.
- **Media:** Prioritize large, optimized background videos to establish the "vibe" immediately.

## Critical Business Logic
- Never remove the "Starter Pack" (£49) CTA from the primary gateway.
- Refer to @business_context.md for all specific gym details, prices, and copy.